{
  "stem": "26111.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then, of course, came my 13th birthday, very shortly after-- well, a year-- a bit more than a year after moving to Berlin.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So my preparation for the-- for the bar mitzvah was already-- that already put me much more in touch with religion and, and the synagogue than, than my parents ever, ever were in touch.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They did.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They did, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, indeed, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The-- at the synagogue, I, I had insisted on-- even though my Hebrew was kind of weak, I had insisted on reading, or singing, rather, a, a part of the-- an excerpt from the Torah, as I had seen others do.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I wasn't going to do any less.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, and I had very good training for that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I got through it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my father, whom I saw in the-- in the audience there, I don't think he came up.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't-- I don't think he came up to the front part.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But, in any event, he seemed to be-- it was a-- it was a funny mix of feelings because he was-- this was all very strange to him.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Ideologically, he was opposed to it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He was areligious, maybe slightly anti, even though he never said that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But, but he was nonetheless impressed because he was conscious of being a Jew.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I don't think he ever reconciled-- poor man.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "This is-- this is-- this is one tragedy of many people that-- in his situation.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I'm sure there were many in Germany because he is not the only German Jew that was-- that thought like he did.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There must have been many-- to, to go to their deaths with those kind of basic questions about their own identity-- is, is a tragedy.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Well, There's a tragedy, too.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
